results.raw: One Student Killed, One Injured in Shooting Outside Education Center at 7450 Penn Ave S, Minneapolis, Minnesota, 55423
results.title: One Student Killed, One Injured in Shooting Outside Education Center

-MuqpADVRQ9umOMMcDYb.text: Incident reported at 7450 Penn Ave S.

-MuqpAE3Dv6pu5oM4Kel.text: Multiple agencies are on scene outside South Education Center.

-Mur0LCnablmse1qR7Fl.text: Police confirmed a shooting took place shortly after noon outside the South Education Center.

nib.text:
One student was killed and a second was critically wounded in a shooting outside Richfieldâ€™s South Education Center.

In a press conference shortly after 2:30 p.m., police and District 287 officials confirmed the shooting.

Police were called to the campus at 7450 Penn Avenue South around 12:07 p.m. 

Arriving officers discovered two students who had been shot on the sidewalk outside of the school, near the front entrance to South Education Center.

Police determined suspects had immediately fled the scene.

Both victims were taken to the hospital via ambulance.

One student was pronounced deceased. The second was in critical condition.

Nearby schools were placed on lockdown as a precaution. Police searched the area and determined there was no further threat.

Police said the shooting is under active investigation and they are searching for suspects.

Parents were instructed to pick up students at Donaldson Park nearby.
